# Parameter documentation for linear models

The documentation for the `alphas` parameter for `RidgeCV` lacks the default value that is defined in constructor of parent class and may be hard to guess. Also it is said to be a Numpy array, while list/ tuple also can be passed (the default value is a tuple).

Some more linear models also lack default value documentation, e.g. alpha and fit_intercept fo RidgeClassifier, so I can also fix them too.

Feel free to send a PR!

@alexitkes Hi Alex, I would like to help. Let me know if you would like to divide and conquer this task or you are going to improve the documentation for all the models that you listed?

Already done much for Ridge, RidgeCV and RidgeClassifier.
@arpanchowdhry Well, documentation for Lasso, ElasticNet and ElasticNetCV also seems to lack default parameter values.

@alexitkes Thanks. Let me take a look at these three models. Also since this is my first issue, I will take a look at your changes for guidance. 

@alexitkes Hi Alex! Are you still looking for help? I'm interested for contributing in this issue.

@vinidixit Sure, there is still some work to do. For example, default values for some parameters of `PassiveAggressiveClassifier` and `PassiveAggressiveRegressor` are not documented and default value for `PassiveAggressiveClassifier.fit_intercept` is documented to be False while actually set to True.

@alexitkes  It seems like there is also some work to do on Least Angle Regression, I'll would like to work on that if you're not already working on it

@alexitkes I have done the documentation and made a PR.please check and reply.Thank you.

I would like to help if any aspect is still open. Please let me know. This is my first attempt.

